OL,3,CWhat is the Bab el-Mandeb Strait and
OL,4,Cwhy is it significant?
OL,6,FThe Bab el-Mandeb, Arabic for "Gate of
OL,7,FTears" or "Gate of Grief", is a
OL,8,Fmaritime strait separating the Horn of
OL,9,FAfrica from the Arabian Peninsula.
OL,11,FIts positioning makes it one of the
OL,12,Fmost important shipping routes in the
OL,13,Fworld.
OL,15,FThe narrow passage forms a key
OL,16,Fcommercial chokepoint, connecting the
OL,17,FRed Sea, which leads to the Suez
OL,18,FCanal, with the Gulf of Aden, which
OL,19,Fopens into the Indian Ocean.
OL,21,FWhere is the Bab el-Mandeb located?
OL,26,@nD@_OUoD@FO]oD@KOUoD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
